\b Licensing FAQ (VelesDB Core License 1.0)\b0\par
\par
This FAQ is provided for convenience and developer guidance only. It does not replace, modify, or supplement the license terms above. In case of any conflict, the license terms prevail. If in doubt, contact the Licensor (Wiscale France \u8212? contact@wiscale.fr).\par
\par
### 1) Can I use VelesDB Core in production?\par
\par
**Yes.** Production use is permitted, including commercial production use, as long as you comply with the license limitations (no Hosted or Managed Service, no Competitive Offering).\par
\par
### 2) Can I use VelesDB Core inside my own SaaS product?\par
\par
**Yes.** If VelesDB Core is used only as an internal component of your SaaS and your customers interact only with your application's interface (not with VelesDB directly), this is permitted.\par
\par
In practice: your customers can use your app's features (search, RAG, recommendations, etc.), but they cannot create collections, manage indexes, run arbitrary queries, or otherwise use VelesDB as a database product.\par
\par
### 3) Can I use VelesDB Core as a backend for a RAG system?\par
\par
**Yes.** Using VelesDB Core to index documents, store embeddings, and retrieve results for a RAG pipeline is a typical permitted use case, as long as end users receive only the generated answers from your application and do not have direct database access.\par
\par
### 4) What is NOT allowed without a commercial license?\par
\par
- Offering VelesDB Core (or a derivative) as a hosted or managed database service (DBaaS, vector DB as a service, managed cluster, etc.).\par
- Operating VelesDB Core for a customer as an MSP, outsourcer, or consultant where the customer has access to VelesDB's core capabilities.\par
- Building and selling a competing database, vector database, search engine, or query engine based on VelesDB Core.\par
- A cloud provider (e.g., AWS, GCP, Azure, or any other) offering VelesDB as a managed database service.\par
\par
If you want to do any of the above, you need an **Enterprise or Premium license**.\par
\par
### 5) Can I expose a public API endpoint that runs vector search against VelesDB Core?\par
\par
**It depends:**\par
\par
- **Allowed:** You expose an endpoint like `/search` or `/recommend` that returns results for your product, without giving customers the ability to create/manage collections, ingest vectors, manage indexes, run arbitrary queries, or administer the database.\par
- **Not allowed without a commercial license:** You expose VelesDB-like capabilities (collections, ingestion, indexing, querying, admin) to third parties in a way that makes your service effectively "VelesDB as a service."\par
\par
### 6) Can I let my customers upload documents, and I index them in VelesDB Core for RAG?\par
\par
**Yes.** As long as customers are using your product's document upload feature and are not given direct access to VelesDB's database capabilities (no collection management, no arbitrary queries, no index administration).\par
\par
### 7) Can a cloud provider offer VelesDB as a managed service?\par
\par
**No, not under this license.** Cloud providers (or any third party) offering VelesDB as a managed database, DBaaS, managed cluster, hosted indexing/query platform, or vector database as a service must obtain a commercial license from Wiscale France.\par
\par
### 8) Can an agency, consultant, or MSP host VelesDB Core for a client?\par
\par
**Not under this license** if the arrangement constitutes a Hosted or Managed Service (including single-customer managed hosting where the client has access to VelesDB's core capabilities). That scenario requires a commercial license.\par
\par
### 9) Can I embed VelesDB Core in a desktop, mobile, or on-prem product I sell?\par
\par
**Yes.** Distributing VelesDB Core bundled with your product is permitted, provided you comply with the license (include the license text and notices), and you are not providing it as a Hosted or Managed Service.\par
\par
### 10) Can I modify VelesDB Core and keep my changes private?\par
\par
**Yes.** The license allows modification. If you distribute a modified version, you must include prominent notices stating that you modified it, and you must provide a copy of the license terms to recipients.\par
\par
### 11) Can I redistribute VelesDB Core?\par
\par
**Yes.** You may redistribute the Software (as-is or modified) through any mechanism (Docker, package managers, Helm charts, etc.), provided:\par
\par
- the license text is included,\par
- copyright notices are preserved,\par
- the software remains under this license,\par
- if modified, modifications are prominently marked.\par
\par
Redistribution does not grant recipients any right to provide the Software as a Hosted or Managed Service.\par
\par
### 12) Can I publish benchmarks of VelesDB Core?\par
\par
**Yes.** You are encouraged to benchmark VelesDB Core. However, public benchmark results must include full disclosure of methodology, dataset, hardware, software version, and configuration. This ensures transparency and reproducibility.\par
\par
### 13) Can I build a competing database product using VelesDB Core?\par
\par
**No.** The No Competitive Offering clause prohibits using the Software to build, sell, or offer a product that competes with VelesDB as a database, vector database, graph database, columnar store, search engine, or query engine.\par
\par
However, using VelesDB Core as an internal component of a non-competing product (e.g., a CRM, an e-commerce platform, a content management system) is permitted.\par
\par
### 14) Can I remove license headers or copyright notices?\par
\par
**No.** You may not alter, remove, or obscure licensing, copyright, or other notices.\par
\par
### 15) Can I use the name "VelesDB" for my fork?\par
\par
**No.** VelesDB\u174? is a registered trademark of Wiscale France. You may not brand your fork, derivative work, or product as "VelesDB" without written permission from Wiscale France. Use of the VelesDB name or logo is subject to applicable trademark law.\par
\par
### 16) What about a multi-tenant service where each tenant only has limited features?\par
\par
If tenants (third parties) get access to a Substantial Set of VelesDB's database, vector database, or query capabilities, it is a Hosted or Managed Service and requires a commercial license, regardless of the number of features exposed per tenant.\par
\par
### 17) What if my service wraps VelesDB behind an API gateway or middleware?\par
\par
The license explicitly covers indirect access through APIs, SDKs, gateways, middleware, service layers, and application wrappers. If the end result is that third parties can use the Software as a database \u8212? regardless of how many layers sit between them and VelesDB \u8212? a commercial license is required.\par
\par
### 18) What if I'm unsure whether my use case is permitted?\par
\par
**Ask.** Contact Wiscale France (contact@wiscale.fr) for clarification or to discuss a commercial license. We want developers to build great things with VelesDB \u8212? we're happy to help you find the right license for your use case.\par
\par
### 19) How do I get an Enterprise or Premium license?\par
\par
Contact Wiscale France (contact@wiscale.fr) to discuss licensing for hosted/managed services, Competitive Offerings, cloud provider partnerships, and other premium use cases.\par
\par
### 20) What is the difference between VelesDB Core, Enterprise, and Cloud?\par
\par
| Tier | License | Use Case |\par
|------|---------|----------|\par
| **VelesDB Core** | This license (source-available) | Internal use, embedding, SaaS backend, development, testing |\par
| **VelesDB Enterprise** | Commercial license | Advanced features, support, hosted/managed services, competitive offerings |\par
