\par
### 21) Can I use VelesDB's graph engine and knowledge graph features in my product?\par
\par
**Yes.** You can use the vector, graph, columnar, and hybrid search features internally within your product. The restriction applies only if you expose those capabilities directly to third parties as a database service, or if you build a competing graph/vector/search product.\par
\par
### 22) Can I embed VelesDB in a browser (WASM), mobile app, or Tauri desktop app?\par
\par
**Yes.** Embedded and local-first use is expressly permitted. VelesDB is designed to run in-process (WASM, iOS, Android, Tauri, server). As long as the Software serves as an internal component of your application, this is a permitted use.\par
\par
### 23) Does the license cover the premium features (Hybrid Search, RBAC, SSO, etc.)?\par
\par
The VelesDB Core license covers VelesDB Core. Premium features (such as RBAC, SSO, GPU Acceleration, Audit Logging, Multi-Tenancy, Encryption at Rest, and Snapshots) are available under VelesDB Enterprise with a separate commercial license. You may not circumvent the licensing mechanism that enforces premium features.\par
\par
### 24) Can I use VelesDB Core's VelesQL query language in my product?\par
\par
**Yes.** Using VelesQL to query data internally within your product is permitted. However, exposing a general-purpose VelesQL endpoint to third parties (allowing them to run arbitrary queries) would constitute providing access to a Substantial Set of the Software's capabilities and is not permitted without a commercial license.\par
\par
### 25) Do I need to display "Powered by VelesDB" on my website or app?\par
\par
**Yes, if your app is public.** Include a link to velesdb.com somewhere visible \u8212? footer, About page, credits, or docs. That's it. No specific size, color, or position required. Just a clickable link that users can find.\par
\par
Want to remove it? An Enterprise license waives the attribution requirement.\par
\par
### 26) What counts as a "public-facing application"?\par
\par
Anything accessible by people outside your organization: a SaaS product, a public website, a mobile app on app stores, a public API. Internal tools and staging environments don't count.\par
\par
### 27) Can I use the VelesDB logo instead of text?\par
\par
**Yes.** Logo or text, your choice \u8212? as long as it links to velesdb.com. Brand assets are at https://velesdb.com/brand.\par
